    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-26T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-26T03:00:00-05:00" n="95"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d95">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.50/4–2646: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Rankin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-26T10:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 26, 1946—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 27—11:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>563. Letter dated April 25 from Minister Coordination Stephanopoulos approves
                    sending three experts suggested <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 480,
                    April 12<note n="90" xml:id="d95fn90">Not printed; it expressed the Department’s
                        belief that the Greek request for the sending of American economic experts
                        should be confirmed by the new Greek Government (868.50/3–646).</note> and
                    expresses gratitude US action.</p>
                <p>Request Dept telegraph names when selected and clarify points raised <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 539, April 21,<note n="91"
                        xml:id="d95fn91">Not printed.</note> second paragraph, to avoid possible
                    misunderstanding.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rankin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
